# Fix Google Sign-In "Cancelled" Error

## Goal
Resolve the "cancelled" error during Google Sign-In by ensuring the correct scopes are requested. The application relies on Google Drive for storage (as seen in [DriveService](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/drive_service.dart#10-247) and [LoginScreen](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/login_screen.dart#11-17) debug prints), but [AuthService](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/auth_service.dart#5-51) currently initializes `GoogleSignIn` without any scopes. This mismatch often leads to authentication failures or subsequent permission errors.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change adds the `drive.driveFileScope` to the Google Sign-In request. Users will see a permission prompt asking for access to Google Drive files. This is expected and necessary for the app to function.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration
#### [MODIFY] [pubspec.yaml](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/pubspec.yaml)
- Increment version to `1.0.2+11`.

#### [MODIFY] [Podfile](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/ios/Podfile)
- Added preprocesser definitions for `permission_handler` (Camera, Photos, Microphone, Notifications). This is essential for the package to compile and link correctly on iOS.

### Auth Service
#### [MODIFY] [auth_service.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/auth_service.dart)
- Added Google Drive scopes to ensure proper permissions during sign-in.

